## Project Context
Paperwork Labs builds products that eliminate paperwork. The venture has four products: FileFree (free tax filing), LaunchFree (free LLC formation), Distill (B2B compliance automation APIs + CPA SaaS), and Trinkets (utility tools). All share infrastructure via a pnpm monorepo.

FileFree starts as a mobile-first free tax prep app — snap a W2, get your completed return in minutes. The long-term product is an AI financial advisor that uses tax filing as the trust-building entry point. LaunchFree files your LLC with the state on your behalf via our State Filing Engine. Distill packages the same infrastructure as B2B APIs for CPAs, law firms, and fintech platforms.

Two co-founders: Founder 1 (Product/Engineering) builds all products and infrastructure. Founder 2 (Partnerships/Revenue) sources and closes financial product partnerships that drive 77% of FileFree revenue. See docs/PARTNERSHIPS.md for the partnerships playbook.

The holding company domain is paperworklabs.com. Product domains: filefree.ai, launchfree.ai, distill.tax, tools.filefree.ai.

## North Stars (Per Product)
- **FileFree**: Own IRS MeF Transmitter (January 2027) — e-file at $0/return. EFIN + ATS certification in progress.
- **LaunchFree**: State Filing Engine covering all 50 states (Summer 2026) — automate LLC formation submission via state APIs, portal automation, and print-and-mail.
- **Distill**: Full B2B compliance automation platform (Summer 2026) — CPA SaaS + Formation API + Tax API + Compliance API at api.distill.tax.
- **Venture-wide**: Build shared compliance infrastructure that powers both free consumer products and paid B2B APIs. The infrastructure IS the product.

## Core Philosophy (Paperwork Labs — applies to all products)
- "Photo to Done in 5 minutes" — every design decision optimizes for speed and simplicity
- Mobile-first, desktop-responsive
- Dark mode by default with vibrant gradients (Linear/Raycast aesthetic, NOT TurboTax boomer energy)
- AI does the work, user just confirms
- Consumer products are FREE FOREVER — this is the acquisition channel, never gate it
- Anxiety-killer — every interaction reduces stress, never adds to it
- Revenue comes from upsells, referrals, and B2B APIs — NOT from consumer filing fees
- FileFree: refund routing, financial referrals, Tax Optimization Plan ($29/yr), audit shield
- LaunchFree: RA credits, banking/payroll/insurance referrals, Compliance-as-a-Service ($49-99/yr)
- Distill: CPA SaaS ($49-199/mo), Formation API ($20-40/filing), Tax API ($5-15/return)
- Every screen should build toward the advisory relationship: "Paperwork Labs knows my finances and helps me make better decisions"

## Tech Stack (DO NOT DEVIATE)

### Monorepo Structure (pnpm workspaces)
```
venture/
  apps/
    filefree/            # filefree.ai — Next.js, consumer tax filing
    launchfree/          # launchfree.ai — Next.js, LLC formation
    distill/             # distill.tax — Next.js, B2B compliance automation
    studio/              # paperworklabs.com — Next.js, command center + portfolio
    trinkets/            # tools.filefree.ai — Next.js SSG, utility tools
  packages/
    ui/                  # shadcn components + 4 brand themes + shared chat widget
    auth/                # shared auth: hooks, middleware, session management
    analytics/           # PostHog + attribution + PII scrubbing
    data/                # 50-state formation + tax JSON configs, Zod schemas
    tax-engine/          # tax calculation, form generators, MeF XML, reconciliation
    document-processing/ # OCR pipeline client, field extraction schemas, bulk upload
    filing-engine/       # State Filing Engine: portal automation, state APIs, Stripe Issuing
    intelligence/        # financial profile, recommendations, campaigns
    email/               # shared email templates (React Email)
  apis/
    filefree/            # Python/FastAPI — consumer tax + Distill B2B routes
    launchfree/          # Python/FastAPI — formation service
    studio/              # Python/FastAPI — command center aggregator
  infra/
    compose.dev.yaml     # Docker Compose (local dev only)
    hetzner/             # n8n + Postiz ops stack
```

### Frontend (all apps)
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Component System**: shadcn/ui (Radix primitives + Tailwind — copy-paste, we own the code)
- **Shared Components**: `packages/ui/` — shared across all apps via pnpm workspace
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4+ with per-product themes via `<body data-theme="filefree|launchfree|distill|studio|trinkets">`
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **AI Streaming**: Vercel AI SDK (`ai` + `@ai-sdk/react`)
- **Charts**: Recharts
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod validation (shadcn Form component)
- **Server State**: @tanstack/react-query — all API calls, caching, polling, optimistic updates
- **Client State**: Zustand — minimal client-only state (auth session, step index, theme)
- **Camera**: Browser MediaDevices API (navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia)
- **PDF Generation**: @react-pdf/renderer

### Backend (all APIs)
- **Framework**: FastAPI (Python 3.11+)
- **ORM**: SQLAlchemy 2.0 with async support
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 15+ (per-product databases + venture database)
- **Cache/Sessions**: Redis
- **Async Processing**: FastAPI BackgroundTasks for MVP (Celery at scale)
- **Migrations**: Alembic (per-API migration chains)
- **B2B Auth**: API key authentication for Distill endpoints (`/api/v1/pro/*`), firm-scoped middleware

### AI/ML Pipeline
- **Document OCR (FileFree + Distill)**: GCP Cloud Vision (`DOCUMENT_TEXT_DETECTION`) → GPT-4o-mini structured extraction → GPT-4o vision fallback (<85% confidence)
- **Image Preprocessing**: Pillow — auto-rotate (EXIF), contrast normalization, resize
- **State Data Extraction (LaunchFree + Distill)**: Gemini 2.5 Flash — extract formation rules, fees, filing steps from state SOS websites
- **Document Generation (LaunchFree)**: GPT-4o-mini — generate Articles of Organization, Operating Agreements from templates
- **Tax Advisory (FileFree)**: GPT-4o — plain-English explanations, personalized tips, advisory content
- **SSN Isolation**: SSN regex-extracted locally from Cloud Vision output — NEVER sent to any LLM. Masked placeholder (XXX-XX-XXXX) in all GPT contexts.
- **Portal Automation (State Filing Engine)**: No AI — Playwright browser automation with deterministic scripts
- **Blended OCR cost**: ~$0.005/doc

### Infrastructure (Zero AWS)
- **Frontend (5 apps)**: Vercel (Hobby → Pro at 5 apps, ~$20/mo)
- **Backend (FileFree API)**: Render Starter ($7/mo, 512MB)
- **Backend (LaunchFree API)**: Render Starter ($7/mo)
- **Portal Automation Worker**: Render (dedicated worker for Playwright, $7/mo)
- **Database**: Neon serverless PostgreSQL (free tier MVP)
- **Sessions**: Upstash serverless Redis (free tier: 500K commands/mo)
- **File Storage**: GCP Cloud Storage (encrypted, 24hr auto-delete lifecycle)
- **Payment Orchestration**: Stripe Issuing — virtual cards for automated state filing fee payment
- **Ops Stack**: Hetzner CX33 ($6/mo) — n8n workflows, Postiz social scheduler, Redis, PostgreSQL
- **DNS/Domains**: filefree.ai, launchfree.ai, distill.tax, paperworklabs.com, tools.filefree.ai
- **Secrets**: Environment variables via .env (never commit)
- **Local Dev**: Docker Compose (`infra/compose.dev.yaml`) — postgres, redis, all APIs, all web apps
- **Production Deploy**: render.yaml (Render Blueprints) + Vercel git deploy
- **Dev Tooling**: Makefile, `.python-version` (3.11), `.node-version` (20), pnpm
- **No AWS**: GCP + Render + serverless providers only

### 50-State Data Layer
- Tax brackets, deductions, credits stored in `packages/data/tax/{year}.json`
- Formation rules, fees, filing steps stored in `packages/data/formation/{state}.json`
- Compliance calendars stored in `packages/data/compliance/{state}.json`
- Each config includes source citations (IRS Rev Proc, state statute)
- Maintained by AI agents via n8n workflows — auto-detect changes, flag for human review
- Validated against IRS Pub 17 (tax) and state SOS websites (formation)

### AI UX Patterns (makes us feel different from TurboTax/LegalZoom)
- AI insights stream in with typewriter effect (Vercel AI SDK useCompletion)
- Pulsing "AI thinking" indicator (animated gradient orb, product-themed color)
- Confidence scores with animated color transitions (red → yellow → green)
- Subtle particle/glow effects around AI-generated content
- Every AI interaction: optimistic UI, stream partial results, never blank loading state

### shadcn/ui Conventions
- Components shared via `packages/ui/` across all apps
- Per-app theme via CSS variables in `globals.css` + `data-theme` attribute (see brand.mdc for palettes)
- Build custom components in each app's `src/components/` — compose from `packages/ui` primitives
- Never install Radix packages directly — always go through shadcn

## Code Style & Conventions

### TypeScript/React
- Use functional components only, never class components
- Use named exports for components, default export only for page components
- File naming: kebab-case for files (e.g., `tax-calculator.ts`), PascalCase for components (e.g., `TaxCalculator.tsx`)
- Directory structure follows Next.js App Router conventions
- All API calls go through @tanstack/react-query hooks wrapping a centralized `lib/api.ts` client
- Use `use client` directive only when necessary (prefer server components)
- All forms use React Hook Form with Zod schemas via shadcn Form component
- Custom hooks go in `hooks/` directory, prefixed with `use`
- Shared types go in `types/` directory

### Python/FastAPI
- Use async def for all route handlers
- Pydantic v2 models for all request/response schemas
- Repository pattern for database access (not raw queries in routes)
- Service layer between routes and repositories for business logic
- All monetary values stored as integers (cents) to avoid floating point issues
- File naming: snake_case everywhere
- Type hints on all function signatures

### Styling Rules
- Mobile-first Tailwind (start with base, add `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints)
- Use CSS variables for theme colors defined in `globals.css` (Tailwind v4 CSS-based config, no tailwind.config.ts)
- Gradient accents per product: FileFree `from-violet-500 to-purple-600`, LaunchFree `from-teal-400 to-cyan-500`, Distill `from-blue-500 to-blue-800`
- Card backgrounds: use shadcn Card component with dark overrides
- Never use arbitrary Tailwind values like `w-[400px]` — use standard utilities
- All interactive elements need hover and focus states
- Minimum touch target: 44x44px for mobile

### Security Rules (CRITICAL — we handle SSNs, EINs, and financial data)
- NEVER log PII (SSN, EIN, full name + address combos, financial data) — PII-scrubbing middleware on all log output
- NEVER store uploaded images longer than necessary (GCP Cloud Storage lifecycle: auto-delete after 24hrs)
- All PII fields encrypted at rest using application-level AES-256 encryption (separate key from DB encryption)
- SSN/EIN displayed as masked in UI, never fully visible after initial entry
- SSNs are never sent to any LLM provider — regex-extracted locally, masked placeholder in all GPT contexts
- Auth exceptions (unauthenticated routes): `/health`, `/auth/*`, `/waitlist`, `/api/v1/waitlist` (per-API)
- Distill B2B routes (`/api/v1/pro/*`): API key auth, firm-scoped middleware, rate limited per key
- Rate limit all endpoints: 5 req/min auth, 20 req/min upload, 5 uploads/day/user, 100 req/min API keys
- CSRF tokens on all state-changing cookie-authenticated endpoints
- hCaptcha on consumer sign-up to prevent bot abuse
- CORS restricted to product's own frontend domain (no cross-product CORS)
- Input validation on EVERY endpoint using Pydantic models
- Account deletion available from day one (CCPA/GDPR) — cascades: Neon DB, GCP Cloud Storage, Upstash sessions
- B2B data isolation: Distill firm data is tenant-isolated. No cross-firm access. No cross-product data usage without explicit consent.
- Never validate SSN/EIN against external sources — prevents stolen identity abuse

## Key Domain Concepts

### FileFree (Tax)
- **Filing**: A single tax return filing attempt (status: draft, processing, review, submitted, accepted, rejected)
- **TaxProfile**: User's tax-relevant information extracted from documents
- **Document**: An uploaded document (W2, DL, 1099, etc.) with extraction results
- **TaxCalculation**: The computed return data (income, deductions, credits, refund/owed)
- **Submission**: The e-file submission record with IRS tracking

### LaunchFree (Formation)
- **Formation**: An LLC formation request (status: draft, documents_ready, submitted, confirmed, failed)
- **StatePortalConfig**: Per-state filing rules, fees, portal URLs, automation tier (API/portal/mail)
- **FilingSubmission**: State filing submission record with tracking and receipt
- **ComplianceCalendar**: Post-formation deadlines (annual reports, franchise tax, RA renewals)

### Distill (B2B)
- **Firm**: A CPA firm or partner organization (multi-tenant root entity)
- **Client**: A firm's client with their tax/formation documents
- **Partner**: A B2B API consumer with API keys and usage tracking
- **BulkUpload**: A batch document upload from a firm for multiple clients

## API Design
- RESTful with consistent response envelope: `{ success: boolean, data: T, error?: string }`
- API versioning via URL prefix: `/api/v1/`
- Consumer auth (FileFree, LaunchFree): HTTP-only secure cookies with SameSite=Lax + CSRF tokens
- B2B auth (Distill): API key in `Authorization: Bearer <key>` header, firm-scoped middleware injects `firm_id`
- File uploads via multipart/form-data to dedicated upload endpoints
- Long-running operations (OCR, state filing) processed via FastAPI BackgroundTasks, client polls via react-query
- Distill API docs hosted at docs.distill.tax (OpenAPI spec, code examples, SDKs)

## Error Handling
- Frontend: sonner toast for user-facing errors, never raw error messages
- Backend: Custom exception classes mapped to HTTP status codes, with PII-scrubbed logging
- All errors logged with correlation IDs for debugging
- User-facing error messages are friendly and actionable ("We couldn't read Box 1 on your W2. Try taking another photo with better lighting.")

## Testing
- Frontend: Vitest + React Testing Library for component tests
- Backend: Pytest with async support, factory_boy for test data
- Tax calculation engine: 100% test coverage required (this is financial data, no bugs allowed)
- Validate tax calculations against IRS Publication 17 worked examples
- Integration tests for the full OCR → calculation pipeline
- Linting: Ruff (Python), ESLint (TypeScript)
- Type checking: mypy (Python), tsc --noEmit (TypeScript)
- Dev commands: `make dev` (start), `make test` (run tests), `make lint` (check), `make format` (fix)
